A recent report in Isolezwa claimed that L vovo was set to answer the call and become a traditional healer.Speaking to TshisaLIVE on Thursday L'vovo confirmed that he would be participating in a traditional ceremony next weekend, but said that it was a personal matter and he could not comment further on it."I'm not talking about what the ceremony is for or what will be happening. You will have to wait and see. I have invited people and they will come and see what it is about. But that will be the first and the last time that I speak about it," he said.L'vovo's management at Mabala Noise also refused to comment on the claims of him becoming a sangoma, saying that it was a private matter. Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.